SIMPLE: wriggle
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Wriggle
<hw>Wrig"gle</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p.
p.</pos> <conjf>Wriggled</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Wriggling</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[Freq. of
<ets>wrig</ets>, probably from OE. <ets>wrikken</ets> to move to and
fro; cf. LG. <ets>wriggeln</ets>, D. <ets>wrikken</ets>, Sw.
<ets>vricka</ets>, Dan. <ets>vrikke</ets>.]</ety> <def>To move the body
to and fro with short, writhing motions, like a worm; to squirm; to
twist uneasily or quickly about.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Both he and successors would often <qex>wriggle</qex> in their
seats,⟦br⟧
as long as the cushion lasted.</q> <rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wriggle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Wriggle
<hw>Wrig"gle</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To move with short, quick
contortions; to move by twisting and squirming; like a worm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Covetousness will <qex>wriggle</qex> itself out at a small
hole.</q> <rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Wriggling</qex> his body to recover⟦br⟧
His seat, and cast his right leg over.</q>
<rj><qau>Hudibras.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wriggle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Wriggle
<hw>Wrig"gle</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Wriggling; frisky; pliant;
flexible.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Their <xex>wriggle</xex>
tails.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wriggle</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Wriggle
<hw>Wrig"gle</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Act of wriggling; a short or quick
writhing motion or contortion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1669 -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wriggler</ent>⟦br⟧
